# CODEOWNERS — who must review changes to which paths.
#
# Pairs with branch protection on `main`: once you enable
# "Require review from Code Owners", a PR that touches an owned path needs an
# approving review from that owner before it can merge.
#
# Matching is last-rule-wins, gitignore-style globs.

# Default: the repo owner owns everything and gates every PR.
*                         @leonlai0831

# --- Marketing KPI module -------------------------------------------------
# Hand the marketing developer ownership of *just* their sandbox, so their PRs
# inside it don't need your review, but anything they touch OUTSIDE it (shared
# DB schema, nav, ui, CLAUDE.md, …) still falls under the `*` rule above = your
# review. To activate:
#   1. Add them as a repo collaborator with Write access.
#   2. Replace USERNAME with their GitHub handle and uncomment the three lines.
# /app/(app)/marketing/     @USERNAME
# /lib/marketing/           @USERNAME
# /components/marketing/    @USERNAME
